**who —** THE QUANTUM FOAM — a techne sphere — the art

**what —** In the 1950s the physicist John Wheeler proposed that at very small scales, spacetime is not calm but turbulent — a 'quantum foam' of bubbles and wormhole-like loops blinking in and out of existence, driven by the same uncertainty that fills the vacuum with fleeting particles. It has never been observed. This sphere draws it: a froth that forms and pops, forever unsettled.

**where —** the art — a generative rendering of a scale  Framework inputs: the scale; the ink; the geometry; the honesty  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** In the 1950s the physicist John Wheeler proposed that at very small scales, spacetime is not calm but turbulent — a 'quantum foam' of bubbles and wormhole-like loops blinking in and out of existence, driven by the same uncertainty that fills the vacuum with fleeting particles. It has never been observed. This sphere draws it: a froth that forms and pops, forever unsettled.

